      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Photograph of the ‘23 August’ cinema in Sovata, central Romania. The building has three entrance doors, with billboards to their left and right.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Sovata (Hung. Szováta) is a spa in Transylvania. The date August 23rd marks the day of the royal coup in Bucharest in 1944, the termination of the alliance with Nazi Germany and the overthrow of the government of dictator Ion Antonescu.</ab>
